h2. Summary

JIRA service desk customer unable to add comment in confluence space although the space has been given anonymous access.

 
h3. Step to replicate
 # Create an user with access 'Restricted Portal';
 # Create a space in Confluence;
 # Set Anonymous access on the space (Space tools) and give them can add comment permission;
 # Try accessing the homepage of the space (created on step 3) using the user 'Restricted Portal' (created on step 2);
 # Try to add comment

 
h3. Observed Behaviour

User unable to add comment

 
h3. Expected Behaviour

User able to add comment

h3. Summary

The following custom CSS styling inserted to a page using

\{style}

and adding Includes within the *Sidebar, header and footer* under the *Look and feel* section used to work. However, it doesn't work anymore on newer versions of Confluence:
{code:java}
body {
	line-height: 27px;
}

.ia-secondary-content,
#create-dialog,
.template-select-container {
	line-height: 1.42857142857143 !important;
}

#header .aui-header {
	background-color: #90a0c1 !important;
	border-bottom-color: #70c0e1 !important;
	color: #ffffff;
}
hr {
	border-bottom: 10px solid #ddd !important;
	margin-top: 20px;
	margin-bottom: 10px;
}
div.cell.normal div.panel.conf-macro.output-block {
	padding: 30px;
}
div.sectionMacroRow + div.columnMacro {
    padding-right: 20px;
}
{code}
h3. Environment

Cloud - Confluence Confluence 1000.842.0
h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Create a page
 # Insert the above CSS using {{style}} to the page.
 # Go to *Sidebar, header and footer*
 # Insert the following CSS on the footer
{noformat}
{include:PORTAL:_Infare-CSS}
{noformat}

h3. Expected Results

The styling should be render as it used to.
h3. Actual Results

Footer displays "unknown macro: \{include}".

Newly provisioned instances fail to complete tenant setup when there is a Media API outage, and continues to be permanently broken after Media API recovers.

